https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/dZaHPNYRTwX8Mbl4o6sTwJcq9Yv.jpg A family's place in the wilderness, outside of time; free-range animals and children, junk and nature, all within the most sublime landscape. The work aims at an idea of freedom, which is reflected in the hand-processed Scope format, but is undercut with a sense of foreboding. There's no particular story; beginning, middle or end, just fragments of lives lived, rituals performed. Ah, Liberty!
